subject: Removal of Casting from CO Expanded Tobacco
summary: The CO expanded tobacco is a new processed tobacco at kk. Tests have indicated that CO expanded tobacco without casing is not different retention. See Attached Memos). Removal of all casing except B-3, will save royalty payments and improve plant operation due to less build up in the sublimator discharge and process fluid.
recommendation: Delete casing except B-3, from the CO expanded tobacco process.
